<div type="definition">
<p>BELIEVE that a PERSON OR ACTION PROBABLY is BAD, LACKING APPROPRIATE PROOF.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The standard current word for suspicion of any kind is yí 疑.</p>
<p>2. Huò 惑 is sometimes used to refer to confusion coupled with suspicion regarding a certain matter.</p>
        </div>
